    "plan_content": "Here is the complete plan for implementing `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Changes (8 files, 2 new)\n\n### New files\n1. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — Core implementation. Iterates over all cache buckets (using `CacheBucket::iter()` + `Python` appended), calls `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` per bucket, prints a left-aligned table, then a `total` row.\n2. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — Integration tests: empty cache returns zeros, populated cache (raw bytes), populated cache (`--human`).\n\n### Modified files\n3. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` and a new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`).\n4. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` to the `PreviewFeature` enum, plus its `as_str()` / `FromStr` / test entries.\n5. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`.\n6. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` → `commands::cache_stats(...)`.\n7. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter.\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Register `mod cache_stats;` under the same `test-python + test-pypi` cfg gate as `cache_size`.\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **`Python` bucket included**: `CacheBucket::iter()` excludes `Python` to protect it from `clean`/`prune`, but `cache stats` adds it so users can see Python download space usage.\n- **Total = sum of buckets**: Slightly less than `cache size` (which walks the whole root including `.lock`, `CACHEDIR.TAG`, etc.), but the per-bucket numbers are self-consistent.\n- **Separate preview flag** (`CacheStats` not `CacheSize`): Each command can graduate from preview independently.",
